subSubSection.paragraph:
Median lobe of aedeagus (
Figs. 59–64
) in lateral view rather evenly arcuate, slightly bent dorsally just at apex; in dorsal view median lobe comparatively wide, only slightly narrowed apically, with terminal lamella (
Figs. 59 & 62
) comparatively wide and short, roundly narrowed posteriorly. Ventral side finely edged laterally in apical part and flattened between margins. Apical orifice in dorsal position, wide apically. Internal sac with two (dorsal and ventral) wide spiny patches apically.

Female genitalia (
Figs. 65 & 66
): gonocoxite comparatively narrow in ventral view, about 0.6 times as long as gonosubcoxite, with wide base.
